Note:
Task #489 gate test: boolean `and`/`or` over BARE truthy operands.

Before #489, the stage1 codegen lowered the canonical short-circuit boolean
operators `and` (TOKEN_AND=30) and `or` (TOKEN_OR=31) to bitwise andq/orq,
and the direct-operand fast path omitted them entirely (so `1 and 0` simply
returned the left operand, 1). Both behaviors are wrong: boolean and/or must
normalize to 0/1 and short-circuit.

This suite asserts the canonical semantics through the result VALUES:

  Case 1: 1 and 0  -> 0   (true AND false = false)
  Case 2: 1 and 1  -> 1   (true AND true  = true)
  Case 3: 0 and 1  -> 0   (false short-circuits)
  Case 4: 0 or 0   -> 0   (false OR false = false)
  Case 5: 1 or 0   -> 1   (true OR false  = true)
  Case 6: 0 or 1   -> 1   (false OR true  = true)
  Case 7: 2 and 3  -> 1   (non-0/1 truthy operands normalize to 1, not 2)
  Case 8: 2 or 0   -> 1   (truthy left normalizes to 1, not the raw 2)
  Case 9: multi-line Return or-chain returns the correct branch (1)
  Case 10: short-circuit: `0 and <side-effect>` does NOT run the side effect
  Case 11: short-circuit: `1 or <side-effect>` does NOT run the side effect

Assertions go through tests/test_utils.runa per convention. Exits 0 with
"ALL TESTS PASSED" when every case holds.
:End Note

Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as T

Note: Module-level counter used to prove short-circuit side-effect ordering.
Let bump_count be 0

Process called "bump" returns Integer:
    Set bump_count to bump_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Multi-line Return or-chain over bare truthy operands. With a=0 and
Note: b=1 the chain is false-or-true, which must return 1 (true), exercising
Note: the multi-line lowering that previously produced garbage.
Process called "or_chain" that takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return a
        or b
End Process

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be T.create_test_results()
    T.begin_suite(results, "compiler.boolean_logic")

    Note: Case 1: 1 and 0 = 0.
    Let c1 be 1 and 0
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 1: 1 and 0", c1, 0)

    Note: Case 2: 1 and 1 = 1.
    Let c2 be 1 and 1
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 2: 1 and 1", c2, 1)

    Note: Case 3: 0 and 1 = 0 (left short-circuits false).
    Let c3 be 0 and 1
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 3: 0 and 1", c3, 0)

    Note: Case 4: 0 or 0 = 0.
    Let c4 be 0 or 0
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 4: 0 or 0", c4, 0)

    Note: Case 5: 1 or 0 = 1.
    Let c5 be 1 or 0
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 5: 1 or 0", c5, 1)

    Note: Case 6: 0 or 1 = 1.
    Let c6 be 0 or 1
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 6: 0 or 1", c6, 1)

    Note: Case 7: non-0/1 truthy operands must normalize to 1, never the raw
    Note: bitwise result (2 & 3 = 2 under the old bug).
    Let c7 be 2 and 3
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 7: 2 and 3 normalizes", c7, 1)

    Note: Case 8: truthy left of OR normalizes to 1, never the raw 2.
    Let c8 be 2 or 0
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 8: 2 or 0 normalizes", c8, 1)

    Note: Case 9: multi-line Return or-chain returns the true branch.
    Let c9 be or_chain(0, 1)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 9: multi-line or-chain", c9, 1)

    Note: Case 10: `0 and bump()` must NOT call bump (short-circuit).
    Set bump_count to 0
    Let c10 be 0 and bump()
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 10: and short-circuit value", c10, 0)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 10: and short-circuit no side-effect", bump_count, 0)

    Note: Case 11: `1 or bump()` must NOT call bump (short-circuit).
    Set bump_count to 0
    Let c11 be 1 or bump()
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 11: or short-circuit value", c11, 1)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 11: or short-circuit no side-effect", bump_count, 0)

    Note: Sanity: when the right operand IS reached, the side effect runs and
    Note: the normalized boolean is 1.
    Set bump_count to 0
    Let c12 be 1 and bump()
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 12: and evaluates right", c12, 1)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 12: and right side-effect ran", bump_count, 1)

    T.print_summary(results)
    Let ok be T.all_passed(results)
    T.destroy_test_results(results)
    If ok is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process
